## (c) Calibrated verdict

**Does the evidence support "9.3v changes idle stream servicing"? ‚Üí NO. Evidence is neutral-to-against.**

| Evidence class | Finding |
|---|---|
| **Documentation** | Only 9.3b docs exist. They already specify: auto-service ON by default, secondary thread feeds streams, IO thread handles reads. No 9.3v delta documented. |
| **Export table** | Full stream-feeding API (`AIL_auto_service_stream`, `AIL_service_stream`, `AIL_serve`, `AIL_IO_thread_handle`, `AIL_set_file_callbacks`, `AIL_set_async_callbacks`, `MilesAsync*`) present in **both**. Delta is event-debug additions + `AIL_background` removal ‚Äî none imported by our exe, none describing a different feed model. |
| **Embedded strings** | Identical IO/thread/stream infrastructure strings in both DLLs; only meaningful diff is version banner + non-streaming event strings. |
| **Changelog** | No 9.3v release notes on disk. |
| **Measured 9.3b behavior** (axiom, not a version comparison) | With auto-service OFF + main-thread `AIL_service_stream` loop: 542 calls ‚Üí **0** sync read-callback invocations; stream got only open's 8 KB read (`CONSULT-35v-AXIOMS.md:51‚Äì52`, `35-04-LOGIN-MUSIC-FOLLOWUP.md:22‚Äì25`). That proves **our 9.3b integration starves**, but says nothing about 9.3v being different. |

**What the evidence does *not* establish:** that Restoration's 9.3v build fixes login music. Restoration working on 9.3v is an **observation outside this diff** ‚Äî it could reflect Debug-vs-Release, provider set, build flags, or integration paths we have not compared here. The L5 RIB crash on our Debug exe with a 9.3v swap also blocks direct runtime A/B of idle stream behavior.

**Bottom line:** There is **no documented or binary-evidenced difference** in *how* `AIL_open_stream` streams are fed at idle between 9.3b and 9.3v. Both expose the same streaming auto-service architecture (secondary/IO background thread, `AIL_service_stream` as the read pump). Adopting 9.3v purely to fix idle stream starvation is **not supported by available evidence**; the measured starvation on 9.3b points at engine/Miles interaction (custom `AIL_set_file_callbacks` + opaque async stream path per `35-04-LOGIN-MUSIC-FOLLOWUP.md:16‚Äì25`), not a evidenced point-release servicing change.
